Orange dwarfs are also very common in our galaxy, they generally have a mass of between 0.5 and 0.8 of the sun and have lower surface temperatures.
Orange dwarfs stay in the main sequence period of their lifespan up to three times longer than yellow dwarfs such as our sun.
Orange dwarf systems are considered very stable environments for the development of planets and the evolutionary process of life.
Orange dwarfs are classified with the letter K.